The estimated models for the location parameter μ with single and combined covariates, the estimated constrained scale (σ) and shape parameters (ξ), and their standard errors (se) are shown in Table 9. Physically, models AMS1 and AMS2 show the additive effects of rainfall and discharge to the location parameter, whereas AMS3 to AMS5 suggests the respective subtractive effects of evaporation, IOD, and SOI on the location parameter. This means that higher rainfall and river inflows may lead to increases in lake levels, whereas higher evaporation and negative phases of IOD and SOI results in lower lake levels.Table 9
